ably nicer to then do the if-statements as a<br /><br />   switch (cram_inode-&gt;mode &amp; S_IFMT) {<br />   case S_IFREG:<br />   ..<br /><br />but what I objected to in the previous patch was doing it multiple<br />times, and moving the nice separate helper function into the caller.<br /><br />So I _think_ you should be able to just do something like this:<br /><br />   ino = cramino(cramfs_inode, offset);<br />   switch (cram_inode-&gt;mode &amp; S_IFMT) {<br />   case S_IFREG:<br />      fops = generic_ro_fops;<br />      aops = &amp;cramfs_aops;<br />      break;<br />   case S_IFDIR:<br />      ...<br />   default:<br />       ino = CRAMINO_UNIQ(offset);<br />   }<br />   inode = iget_locked(sb, ino);<br />   if (inode &amp;&amp; (inode-&gt;i_state &amp; I_NEW)) {<br />      inode-&gt;i_ops = iops;<br />      inode-&gt;i_fops = fops;<br />      inode-&gt;i_data.a_ops = aops;<br />      setup_inode(inode, cramfs_inode, cramfs_inode-&gt;size);<br />    }<br /><br />or whatever?<br /><br />                   Linus<br />--<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.kernel.org<br />More majordomo info at  <a href="http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html">http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html</a><br />Please read the FAQ at  <a href="http://www.tux.org/lkml/">http://www.tux.org/lkml/</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
